oacIpServicesConfigMIB.name: oacIpServicesConfigMIB

revisions.description: This MIB defines configuration capabilities relating to IP services : DHCP client, DNS, ARP .

oacIpServicesConfigMIB.contactinfo: Pascal KESTELOOT Postal: ONE ACCESS 381 Avenue du Gnral de Gaulle 92140 Clamart, France FRANCE Tel: (+33) 01 41 87 70 00 Fax: (+33) 01 41 87 74 00 E-mail: pascal.kesteloot@oneaccess-net.com

oacIpDnsConfigMainAdd.name: oacIpDnsConfigMainAdd
oacIpDnsConfigMainAdd.description: The main domain server IP address

oacIpDnsConfigSndAdd.name: oacIpDnsConfigSndAdd
oacIpDnsConfigSndAdd.description: The secondary domain server IP address

oacIpDnsConfigTimeout.name: oacIpDnsConfigTimeout
oacIpDnsConfigTimeout.description: The duration (default is 150 seconds) to wait for the name server answer

oacDhcpClientBroadcastFlag.name: oacDhcpClientBroadcastFlag
oacDhcpClientBroadcastFlag.description: Activation or not of the broadcast flag in DHCP Offer/Ack message, so that the server is made aware if the DHCP packets are unicast or broadcast

oacDhcpVendorId.name: oacDhcpVendorId
oacDhcpVendorId.description: To include the option 60 within the DISCOVER messages and to append a proprietary vendor-ID string

oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceTable.name: oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceTable
oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceTable.description: This table contains the Additional DHCP Client configuration on interfaces. The ifIndex in the INDEX clause identifies the interface where these options are applied.

oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceEntry.name: oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceEntry
oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceEntry.description: An entry in this table defines the additional option(s) sent by the DHCP Client.

oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceIfName.name: oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceIfName
oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceIfName.description: The name of the interface where the Dhcp Client is associated. Same as ifDescr from IF-MIB

oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceIgnoreDefRoute.name: oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceIgnoreDefRoute
oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceIgnoreDefRoute.description: Do not insert default route in routing table

oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceUserClassId.name: oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceUserClassId
oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceUserClassId.description: Insert option 77 user class, if void option 77 is not inserted

oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceRowStatus.name: oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceRowStatus
oacIpDhcpClientInterfaceRowStatus.description: The row status for this rule.

oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceTable.name: oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceTable
oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceTable.description: This table contains the DHCP Client configuration on interfaces. The ifIndex in the INDEX clause identifies the interface where the DHCP Client is activated.

oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceEntry.name: oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceEntry
oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceEntry.description: An entry in this table defines the interface where the DHCP Client is activated.

oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceActivate.name: oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceActivate
oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceActivate.description: Activate the DHCP Client on the interface.

oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceIfName.name: oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceIfName
oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceIfName.description: The name of the interface where the Dhcp Client is associated. Same as ifDescr from IF-MIB

oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceClientId.name: oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceClientId
oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceClientId.description: Set of the Client Identifier. The optional argument indicates which MAC address shall be used in the DHCP DISCOVER message. When the optional client-id argument is not present, the DHCP DISCOVER message uses the MAC address of the interface otherwise if present it uses the client-id string value.

oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceRowStatus.name: oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceRowStatus
oacIpDhcpAddClientInterfaceRowStatus.description: The row status for this rule.

oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigTable.name: oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigTable
oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigTable.description: This table contains the Proxy ARP configuration on interfaces. The ifIndex in the INDEX clause identifies the interface where Proxy ARP is applied

oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigEntry.name: oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigEntry
oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigEntry.description: An entry in this table defines the interface where the Proxy ARP is configured.

oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigIfName.name: oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigIfName
oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigIfName.description: The name of the interface where Proxy Arp is activated. Same as ifDescr from IF-MIB

oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigRowStatus.name: oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigRowStatus
oacIpProxyArpInterfaceConfigRowStatus.description: The Row Status for this rule.

oacIpIcmpRedirConfigRedirRoutesActivate.name: oacIpIcmpRedirConfigRedirRoutesActivate
oacIpIcmpRedirConfigRedirRoutesActivate.description: Enable learning icmp redirect routes. It is possible to define the timeout (in seconds) of redirect routes See below the meaning of the different values : - Default timeout 180s - 0 Value to disable learning icmp redirect routes (default behaviour) - <1-4294967295> Timeout of redirect routes (seconds)

oacIpIcmpRedirConfigRateLimitUnreach.name: oacIpIcmpRedirConfigRateLimitUnreach
oacIpIcmpRedirConfigRateLimitUnreach.description: rate limit icmp messages generated. See below the meaning of the different values : - Default value 500ms - 0 Default behaviour - <1-4294967295> Once per milliseconds
